Sentencas: Ce0.8Sm0.15Ca0.05O1.875 (S15C05DC) and Ce0.8Sm0.15Ca0.05O1.875 (S15S05DC) electrolytes were synthesized by a solid-state reaction and used to prepare solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Sr2+ doping on the microstructure and cell performance of samaria-doped ceria electrolytes used in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructures and electrical properties of the electrolytes were analyzed by XRD, SEM, thermal analyzer, thermomechanical analysis, TEM, electrochemical analysis, and impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Sr2+ doping on the microstructure and cell performance of samaria-doped ceria electrolytes used in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum densification strain rates of S15C05DC and S15S05DC were 10.6 x 10(-3)-11.1 x 10(-3) min(-1) at 1330 degrees C and 8.3 x 10(-3)-8.7 x 10(-3) min(-1) at 1300 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Sr2+ doping on the microstructure and cell performance of samaria-doped ceria electrolytes used in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of Ca2+ or Sr2+ could help in accelerating CeO2 sintering.
Titulo: Effect of Ca2+ and Sr2+ doping on the microstructure and cell performance of samaria-doped ceria electrolytes used in solid oxide fuel cells
